title: For Sale:  FN FiveSeven RARE IOM Model
postcontent:
This is an Fn FiveSeven 5.7x28mm IOM pistol. This is the IOM (Individual Officer's Model) a little over 4000 of these were made making it a very rare FiveSeven, perfect for any collector. Production of the IOM was stopped shortly after the FiveSeven hit the civilian market as FN upgraded to the newer USG model, I favor the IOM myself. This is the gun that gun control groups were up in arms about 10 years ago, the one you've heard all about. Claims were made its rounds were "armor piercing" by gun control groups. Shortly after this some types of ammunition were no longer imported (including the SS195 ammo that I am including 162 rounds of with the gun) 

I really am not sure how many rounds I have shot through it, I doubt it to be anything over a few hundred as I only shoot 10-20 rounds through it when I even take it out of the safe. It is is excellent condition. Is in original case, with 2x 10 round magazines, factory cleaning kit, all factory documentation, and one spent shell from the factory. Only thing missing from the case is the original lock it came with.

Including 370x SS197 blue tip horniday rounds and 162x SS195LF (lead free version of the SS192)

title: For Sale:  Ruger LCR 22LR, Hi Velocity 22LR ammo, pocket holster
postcontent:
Well, I've finally decided to go ahead and sell my beloved LCR 22LR in order to make way for some life changes. I've had the gun for a little over a year and have put a few bricks of 22lr through it over that time. I also pocket-carried it occasionally in a desantis pocket holster, although that was pretty rare. I consider myself to be pretty OCD about how I take care of my guns, so it was cleaned very thoroughly after every range session and when I carried it, and was then promptly put back in the safe in my bedroom closet. The gun has always functioned flawlessly and is in excellent condition. I'm also including 200 rounds of Remington Yellowjacket 22lr, 100rds of Remington Viper 22LR, and 50rds of federal spitfire 22lr. The Yellowjacket ammo was what I carried in it the few times I did carry because all my research last year pointed to that being the most powerful 22lr ammo out of a super-short barrel (cci stingers etc carry more energy out of longer barrels but not out of ones less than ~3" or so based on everything I've read). I'm also including the desantis pocket holster I used the few times I did carry it since I don't have any need for it now. 

I haven't been following gun/ammo prices all that closely these days but I'm hoping to get $440 for all of it. Please feel free to send me an email if you have any questions or would like more pictures. Thanks!
